         <abstract>
            <p>A shadowing result is formulated in such a way that it applies in the context of numerical approximations of semilinear parabolic problems. The qualitative behavior of temporally and spatially discrete finite element solutions of a reaction-diffusion system near a hyperbolic equilibrium is then studied. It is shown that any continuous trajectory is approximated by an appropriate discrete trajectory, and vice versa, as long as they remain in a sufficiently small neighborhood of the equilibrium. Error bounds of optimal order in the L&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; and H&lt;sup&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt; norms hold uniformly over arbitrarily long time intervals.</p>
          </abstract>
